Conclusion: exactly 2 genuine case-sensitivity weakenings (lines 137, 255,
matching the host's diagnosis) plus 1 additional defensive hardening (line
256, not a live divergence but converted for consistency). All other
`-match`/`-notmatch`/`-replace`/`-eq`/`-ne` sites are safe by construction
(digit-only or whitespace-only patterns, or numeric/null comparisons).

--- 2. Fixes applied (via Edit tool only) ---

Line 137: `-notmatch` -> `-cnotmatch`
Line 255: `-match` -> `-cmatch`
Line 256: `-replace` -> `-creplace` (defensive hardening)

--- 3. Parity verification (3a): mismatched-case status rejection ---

Built two full domain/ fixtures (via Initialize-LoopFixture -Profile
greenfield, mutating only Domain-Model-Status) plus a read-only copy of the
unedited domain-review-precheck.sh into each (never modifying the real
repo path or the real .sh file).

3a-i. Domain-Model-Status: pending (lowercase)
  .sh original:              ERROR: domain-review-precheck: context-map.md must declare a recognized Domain-Model-Status   EXIT:1
  .ps1 port (named params):  ERROR: domain-review-precheck: context-map.md must declare a recognized Domain-Model-Status   EXIT:1
  .ps1 port (array-splat):   ERROR: domain-review-precheck: context-map.md must declare a recognized Domain-Model-Status   EXIT:1
  Result: exit code MATCH (1), stderr text byte-identical MATCH.

3a-ii. Domain-Model-Status: APPROVED (uppercase)
  .sh original:              ERROR: domain-review-precheck: context-map.md must declare a recognized Domain-Model-Status   EXIT:1
  .ps1 port (named params):  ERROR: domain-review-precheck: context-map.md must declare a recognized Domain-Model-Status   EXIT:1
  .ps1 port (array-splat):   ERROR: domain-review-precheck: context-map.md must declare a recognized Domain-Model-Status   EXIT:1
  Result: exit code MATCH (1), stderr text byte-identical MATCH.

Counterfactual confirmation (isolated regex probe, no file I/O):
  "pending" -notmatch '^(Pending|Reviewed|Approved)$'  => False (pre-fix operator would have INCORRECTLY ACCEPTED "pending")
  "pending" -cnotmatch '^(Pending|Reviewed|Approved)$' => True  (fixed operator correctly rejects)
  "APPROVED" -notmatch '^(Pending|Reviewed|Approved)$'  => False (pre-fix operator would have INCORRECTLY ACCEPTED "APPROVED")
  "APPROVED" -cnotmatch '^(Pending|Reviewed|Approved)$' => True  (fixed operator correctly rejects)

--- 3b. Parity verification: mismatched-case previous-round directory
    (the --reset scan fix, line 255) ---

Built a --reset scenario: attempt-1 with ONLY a mixed-case "ROUND-3"
subdirectory (containing a domain-review-contract.json with verdict PASS),
then invoked `--attempt 2 --round 1 --reset`.

  .sh original:              ERROR: domain-review-precheck: previous attempt has no terminal round   EXIT:1
  .ps1 port (named, -Reset): ERROR: domain-review-precheck: previous attempt has no terminal round   EXIT:1
  Result: exit code MATCH (1), stderr text byte-identical MATCH -- the
  mixed-case "ROUND-3" directory is correctly NOT recognized as a valid
  round-N terminal directory by either tool, matching the .sh original's
  case-sensitive `find -name 'round-*'` + sed extraction semantics.

Counterfactual confirmation (isolated regex probe):
  "ROUND-1" -match '^round-[1-3]$'  => True  (pre-fix operator would have INCORRECTLY matched "ROUND-1")
  "ROUND-1" -cmatch '^round-[1-3]$' => False (fixed operator correctly excludes it)
  "round-2" -cmatch '^round-[1-3]$' => True  (fixed operator still correctly matches the real, correctly-cased name)

